OLA - Open Lighting Architecture
================================

    * https://www.openlighting.org/

Download and install:

    * https://www.openlighting.org/ola/getting-started/downloads/
    * https://www.openlighting.org/ola/linuxinstall/

The codebase:

    * https://github.com/OpenLightingProject/ola


How to build and install:
=========================

1a. Download repo

   $ git clone https://github.com/OpenLightingProject/ola.git ola
   $ git checkout 0.10.2

1b. Download latest release from https://github.com/OpenLightingProject/ola/releases

   $ wget https://github.com/OpenLightingProject/ola/releases/download/0.10.2/ola-0.10.2.tar.gz

2. Install build dependencies

        $ bash-completion pkg-config python

   $ apt install build-essential debhelper autotools-dev bison flex uuid-dev libcppunit-dev libprotobuf-dev libprotoc-dev python-protobuf protobuf-compiler libftdi-dev libusb-1.0-0-dev devscripts fakeroot dh-autoreconf pkg-config bash-completion

3. Build package

   $ dpkg-buildpackage -b -us -uc

   # Which runs a variant of:

   ./configure --disable-all-plugins --enable-dummy --enable-usbdmx --disable-http --enable-python-libs --disable-doxygen-doc --disable-java-libs

4. Install packages and dependencies on target

   $ sudo dpkg -i libola1_*.deb ola_*.deb ola-python_*.deb

5. Configure ola and setup universe

   # ola_dev_info
Device 1: Dummy Device
  port 0, OUT Dummy Port, RDM supported
Device 2: Anyma USB Device
  port 0, OUT, patched to universe 0

  # ola_plugin_info
   Id	Plugin Name
--------------------------------------
    1	Dummy
   12	USB
--------------------------------------

  Patch

  # ola_patch --device 2 --port 0 --universe 0

  # nano /var/lib/ola/conf/ola-port.conf

    12-2-O-0 = 0

  Plugin 12 - device 2 - output - port 0 = universe 0

  It is possible that this isn't needed, as a reboot seems to have update the information. Then perhaps
  just the ola_patch is enough

  Verify with

  # ola_dmxconsole
